<subSubSection id="AD76060E934C595000B9F5DE6E0E102B" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FFA51F6D6860EE381B08DEDE1A60F0D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="196CBE84B4B1E1B8A3C37B2BB9CE2086" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
The species (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="74869545D28BA5C0890CE150886868ED" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F5979086" captionText="Figure 9. Selected habitus illustrations of Gerromorpha of Mindoro A. Limnogonus nitidus; B. Limnometra nigripennis nigripennis; C. Tenagogonus sp. (mutilated specimen); D. Rheumatogonus luzonicus; E. Metrocoris tenuicornis. Scale bars 10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467156" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">9</figureCitation>
A) is widespread in the Philippines, Maldives, India, Sri Lanka, southern China and Indonesia (
<bibRefCitation id="5E77223D8BCE020E15538E0E33719515" author="Damgaard, J." journalOrPublisher="Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="251 - 281" refId="B5980461" refString="Damgaard, J., Moreira, F. F., Weir, T. A., Zettel, H., 2014. Molecular phylogeny of the pond skaters (Gerrinae), discussion of the fossil record and a checklist of species assigned to the subfamily (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae). Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 45: 251 - 281" title="Molecular phylogeny of the pond skaters (Gerrinae), discussion of the fossil record and a checklist of species assigned to the subfamily (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae)" volume="45" year="2014">Damgaard et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
), with the first records from Cambodia recently documented by 
<bibRefCitation id="115E8AA56F92C191D1F0C5D13DB1F34C" author="Zettel, H." journalOrPublisher="Aquatic Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="21 - 48" refId="B5979777" refString="Zettel, H., Phauk, S., Kheam, S., Freitag, H., 2017. Checklist of the aquatic Hemiptera (Heteroptera: Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha) of Cambodia, with descriptions of new species of Microvelia Westwood, 1834 and Ranatra Fabricius, 1790. Aquatic Insects 38: 21 - 48" title="Checklist of the aquatic Hemiptera (Heteroptera: Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha) of Cambodia, with descriptions of new species of Microvelia Westwood, 1834 and Ranatra Fabricius, 1790" volume="38" year="2017">Zettel et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. See Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DBB88B6E21935E9469B45E458E039634" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F5979090" captionText="Figure 8. Distribution of the collecting sites of Gerromorpha material (part 2) treated in this study." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.8.e56883.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/467248" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">8</figureCitation>
for our additional records.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8A4B0756E3FCBEB261FEAA8990F73B81" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="9FE2CB154E7B74C31CEB4BD0EC7F3858" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06995C16DFBCCC407BAA5784E2EE2C4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
Refer to 
<bibRefCitation id="CEDD096DD8AA16E4A4169B2128CA8575" author="Cheng, L." journalOrPublisher="Raffles Bulletin of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="129 - 148" refId="B5980308" refString="Cheng, L., Yang, C. M., Andersen, N. M., 2001. Guide to the aquatic Heteroptera of Singapore and Peninsular Malaysia. I. Gerridae and Hermatobatidae. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 49 (1): 129 - 148" title="Guide to the aquatic Heteroptera of Singapore and Peninsular Malaysia. I. Gerridae and Hermatobatidae" volume="49" year="2001">Cheng et al. (2001)</bibRefCitation>
for the identification.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="406401E39B24526AE111C5611F321112" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="F9B3E55297F341BE514CE3861AD9EDBB" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Habitat</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B0722B8B23C820A1C79F0B69DDE351C" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">
In the Oriental realm, most species of 
<taxonomicName id="E94810C5BF7839D630E18F28D6C71DB5" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Limnogonus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Limnogonus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="81B6779BE0BBF95933052CCF30F89CA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Limnogonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="881457A392172F89471123F9CCAA3498" originalValue="StÃ¥l">Stal</normalizedToken>
, 1868 prefer sheltered places in standing waters, which makes them somewhat gregarious. 
<taxonomicName id="E9F73C5888F1494420B677CE03FE894B" baseAuthorityName="Mayr" baseAuthorityYear="1865" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Limnogonus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Limnogonus nitidus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis id="DC4A311456D7CE19BB837B379759BC17" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">Limnogonus nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Mayr, 1865) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="0C050AF02118B1B91404CC352ED01510" author="Mayr, G. L." journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" pagination="429 - 446" refId="B5982173" refString="Mayr, G. L., 1865. Diagnosen Neuer Hemipteren II. Verhandlungen der zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 15: 429 - 446" title="Diagnosen Neuer Hemipteren II" volume="15" year="1865">Mayr 1865</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="581BA10BC92B237FEFB7CA77EA4820A5" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="L. fossarum" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fossarum">
<emphasis id="B6869E31607E9A8E86E9679645AB79D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883">L. fossarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1775) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="32C539D0A73F52B21559191D78EE7407" author="Fabricius, J. C." journalOrPublisher="Entomographien" pageId="0" pageNumber="56883" refId="B5982164" refString="Fabricius, J. C., 1775. Systema Entomologiae, Sistens Insectorvm Classes, Ordines, Genera, Species, Adiectis Synonymis, Locis, Descriptonibus, Observationibus. In: Flensburgi et Lipsiae: Kort." title="Systema Entomologiae, Sistens Insectorvm Classes, Ordines, Genera, Species, Adiectis Synonymis, Locis, Descriptonibus, Observationibus" volumeTitle="Flensburgi et Lipsiae: Kort." year="1775">Fabricius 1775</bibRefCitation>
) are probably the only Oriental species of the genus that successfully colonise intermittent habitats.
</paragraph>
